      "message": "notation: C[change-id]rev@ps  \u003d\u003d CL with specific change-id and revision/ps pair.\n\nThen think I created it like this once\n\ncreate local chain of:\n  base \u003c-  r1      \u003c- r2\nbut specify Change-Id only in r2 to be [B].     \nupload them, and get back auto-generated change-id [A] for r1, s.t.  \n          C[A]r1@1 \u003c- C[B]r2@2\n\nnow create r3 with r2 as parent and specify change-id: A.\nNow push r3. GoB will end up with C[A]r3@2, whose parent is C[B]r2@1, whose parent is C[A]r1@1.\n\nOnce you add merge commits to the menu, I\u0027d rather code CV defensively than rely on Gerrit to disallow these shenanigans.",
